---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="In Remembrance - University of Michigan Mars Rover Team" showFooter={false}>
  <style>
    @keyframes fadeInUp {
      from {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(20px);
      }
      to {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(0);
      }
    }

    @keyframes gentlePulse {
      0%, 100% { opacity: 0.4; }
      50% { opacity: 0.7; }
    }

    .fade-in {
      animation: fadeInUp 1s ease-out forwards;
    }

    .fade-in-delay-1 { animation-delay: 0.2s; opacity: 0; }
    .fade-in-delay-2 { animation-delay: 0.4s; opacity: 0; }
    .fade-in-delay-3 { animation-delay: 0.6s; opacity: 0; }
    .fade-in-delay-4 { animation-delay: 0.8s; opacity: 0; }

    .star-field {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      overflow: hidden;
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    .star {
      position: absolute;
      width: 2px;
      height: 2px;
      background: white;
      border-radius: 50%;
      animation: gentlePulse 3s ease-in-out infinite;
    }

    .photo-frame {
      position: relative;
    }

    .photo-frame::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      inset: -3px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(251, 196, 33, 0.3), rgba(0, 39, 76, 0.5), rgba(251, 196, 33, 0.3));
      border-radius: 12px;
      z-index: -1;
    }
  </style>

<div class="relative min-h-screen bg-linear-to-b from-[#000814] via-[#001d3d] to-[#000814] pt-24 pb-20 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="star-field">
      <div class="star" style="top: 10%; left: 15%; animation-delay: 0s;"></div>
      <div class="star" style="top: 20%; left: 80%; animation-delay: 0.5s;"></div>
      <div class="star" style="top: 35%; left: 25%; animation-delay: 1s;"></div>
      <div class="star" style="top: 45%; left: 90%; animation-delay: 1.5s;"></div>
      <div class="star" style="top: 60%; left: 10%; animation-delay: 2s;"></div>
      <div class="star" style="top: 75%; left: 70%; animation-delay: 0.3s;"></div>
      <div class="star" style="top: 85%; left: 40%; animation-delay: 0.8s;"></div>
      <div class="star" style="top: 15%; left: 55%; animation-delay: 1.2s;"></div>
      <div class="star" style="top: 50%; left: 5%; animation-delay: 1.8s;"></div>
      <div class="star" style="top: 90%; left: 85%; animation-delay: 2.2s;"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <header class="text-center mb-16 fade-in">
        <p class="text-michigan-maize/70 uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-sm mb-4">In Loving Memory</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-white font-light tracking-wide">
          Jacqueline Tardif
        </h1>
        <div class="mt-6 flex items-center justify-center gap-4">
          <span class="h-px w-16 bg-linear-to-r from-transparent to-michigan-maize/50"></span>
          <span class="text-michigan-maize/60 text-lg">1988 - 2021</span>
          <span class="h-px w-16 bg-linear-to-l from-transparent to-michigan-maize/50"></span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="flex justify-center mb-16 fade-in fade-in-delay-1">
        <div class="photo-frame">
          <img
            src="/Jackie.jpeg"
            alt="Jackie Tardif"
            class="rounded-lg shadow-2xl max-w-sm w-full"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <blockquote class="text-center mb-16 fade-in fade-in-delay-2">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-white/70 italic font-light leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          "Per aspera ad astra"
        </p>
        <p class="text-michigan-maize/50 mt-3 text-sm tracking-wider">Through hardships to the stars</p>
      </blockquote>

      <div class="h-px w-32 mx-auto bg-linear-to-r from-transparent via-michigan-maize/30 to-transparent mb-16 mt-8"></div>

      <article class="space-y-8 text-white/80 leading-relaxed text-lg fade-in fade-in-delay-3">
        <p>
          The MRover team honors the memory of <strong class="text-white font-normal">Jacqueline Tardif</strong>,
          a graduate of Michigan's Aerospace Engineering Program and former MRover president, who passed away
          due to Covid-19 complications in January of 2021.
        </p>

        <p>
          Jackie served as team lead from 2010 to 2013, a pivotal era in the team's history. Her extraordinary
          dedication was responsible for much of the team's foundations in its early days. We owe MRover's
          official establishment as a WSTPC team to Jackie, as well as the funding she worked tirelessly to
          secure for building the team's first rovers.
        </p>

        <p>
          Following her graduation, Jackie pursued her passion for space at the Aerospace Corporation in
          El Segundo, California, where she served as a lead mechanical engineer. There, she designed and
          built satellites, two of which were launched into orbit from the International Space Station,
          a testament to her remarkable skill and dedication.
        </p>

        <p>
          Beyond her professional accomplishments, Jackie devoted herself to giving back. She spent her spare
          time working with special needs children through horseback riding programs and STEM outreach
          initiatives, inspiring the next generation just as she inspired all of us.
        </p>
      </article>

      <div class="h-px w-32 mx-auto bg-linear-to-r from-transparent via-michigan-maize/30 to-transparent my-16"></div>

      <footer class="text-center fade-in fade-in-delay-4 flex flex-col items-center">
        <p class="text-white/60 max-w-md text-balance">
          Jackie's full obituary and donation links to Ride to Fly and the National Math and Science Initiative can be found at:
        </p>
        <a
          href="https://www.legacy.com/us/obituaries/washingtonpost/name/jacqueline-tardif-obituary?pid=197677974"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 border border-michigan-maize/30 text-michigan-maize hover:bg-michigan-maize/10 transition-colors duration-300 rounded"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          <span>Read Full Obituary</span>
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
